  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison ponders Mrs. Sarah Thurber Benson&apos;s bereavement, loss, and Christian hope. Garrison is uneasy because of the absence of news from Henry Egbert Benson. The ladies of the Anti-Slavery Society made $542 in one day at their annual fair. Garrison lists the names of the ladies who superintended the tables at the fair. Garrison writes: &quot;At the last New-England Anti-Slavery Convention, the Boston Female Society nobly agreed to raise one thousand dollars for the Massachusetts Society within a year. They have already redeemed their pledge!&quot;</subfield>
